Namaste React Course by Akshay Saini
Chapter 03 - Laying the Foundation

Q. What is JSX?
=> JSX is JavaScript XML which allows us to write HTML-like code in JS and place them in DOM without using createElement and appendChild methods.

Ex: Without using JSX
const element = React.createElement("h1", {}, "Hello, I am not using JSX!");
const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
root.render(element);

Ex: Using JSX
const element = <h1>I am Using JSX</h1>;
const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
root.render(element);


Q. Superpowers of JSX
=> 1. It allows us to write HTML-like code inside JS
   2. JavaScript expressions can be used inside JSX with curly braces "{}"

Ex: const element = <h1>{10 + 5}</h1>

Q. Role of type attribute in a script tag? What options can I use there?
=> Type attribute is used to identify the type of script tag and content between them 

  Different type attribute in <script></script> tag:
  1. module
  2. text/javascript
  3. text/ecmascript
  4. text/babel

